    "description": "The Cisco LWAPP Aironet 1131 & 1242 access points deliver the versatility, high capacity, security, and enterprise-class features required for small, medium and large Government deployments. In FIPS 140-2 mode of operation, the Cisco APs support the LWAPP, MFP, IEEE 802.11i & IEEE 802.1x standards & AES for WPA2 encryption. WPA2 is the Wi-Fi Alliance certification for interoperable, standards-based WLAN security. The Cisco APs are also Wi-FI CERTIFIED for IEEE 802.11a, IEEE 802.11b and IEEE 802.11g radio standards.",
